WEBVTT

00:02.703 --> 00:03.702
- I had intercourse with steve.

00:03.837 --> 00:05.637
I just don't think that
I'm good enough for you.

00:05.639 --> 00:08.773
- The guy was guilty!
- But you beat up a kid!

00:08.809 --> 00:11.876
- You can't protect me? You're
supposed to be my partner.

00:11.912 --> 00:13.645
- Looks like a teenage boy
moved in around here.

00:13.681 --> 00:15.514
- I didn't think
you'd be back yet.

00:15.583 --> 00:17.116
- So a teenage boy did move?

00:17.118 --> 00:19.351
- Your daughter is smuggling
drugs for the pandilla quince.

00:19.353 --> 00:21.920
- You have to let her go.
- We'll see what we can do.

00:21.989 --> 00:24.790
- This is the place that's going
to save my reputation.

00:24.859 --> 00:25.757
I'll support the funding.

00:25.826 --> 00:27.725
- So, adeline has someone inside

00:27.762 --> 00:29.194
Covering her tracks...

00:29.263 --> 00:31.063
- Which means the oce
has a dirty cop.

00:32.500 --> 00:34.333
- Where's my mother?
- She's with me.

00:34.335 --> 00:37.536
I need you to put it in the
system that I've been arrested.

00:37.671 --> 00:39.471
- If adeline killed
her own brother, she will kill

00:39.507 --> 00:41.573
My mother in a heartbeat.
Take ten minutes,

00:41.708 --> 00:43.007
Go grab a sandwich, I got you.

00:43.744 --> 00:45.610
I'm officially corrupt.

00:45.646 --> 00:48.480
- I just want you to know that
word spread about my arrest,

00:48.615 --> 00:50.382
Just like we planned.
- You're under arrest.

00:50.384 --> 00:52.484
Oh, my god, mom. You're okay.

00:52.553 --> 00:54.752
- I'm back, and if you don't
mind, I'd like my seat.

00:54.789 --> 00:57.689
- I'm gonna take you up on that
job offer. Head of security.

00:57.691 --> 00:59.858
- You know that cop, the one
who tried to frame me

00:59.993 --> 01:01.760
For the shooting? He's here.

01:01.829 --> 01:03.762
- This vip terminal
is the coyotes' new way

01:03.897 --> 01:04.763
Of smuggling in pink coke.

01:04.832 --> 01:05.930
- I guess you get to see

01:05.966 --> 01:06.965
Boss man.
(laughs)

01:06.967 --> 01:08.266
- So nice to see you,
deputy mayor.

01:19.513 --> 01:22.514
- Hmm, get me out of this
god forsaken city

01:22.649 --> 01:24.516
With the psychotic
book-clubbers.

01:24.651 --> 01:27.452
Mark my words, this never
would've happened in florida.

01:27.521 --> 01:29.922
- I think you're just as likely
to get abducted in florida.

01:30.057 --> 01:31.723
I mean, do you read
people magazine?

01:31.859 --> 01:35.127
- I intend to drive into my
gated condo and resume a nice,

01:35.196 --> 01:38.063
Quiet life of golfing,
and gardening, and g&ts.

01:38.132 --> 01:41.567
- Mom. You really were
quite remarkable.

01:41.569 --> 01:43.635
What I'm trying to say is...

01:43.637 --> 01:44.970
You're my hero.

01:45.973 --> 01:49.207
Really, you are so smart,
and funny...

01:49.276 --> 01:51.543
(chuckling)
...And interesting.

01:51.678 --> 01:53.178
And I think you're really kind.

01:53.247 --> 01:54.679
I mean, albeit in your
own particular way.

01:54.715 --> 01:56.381
- Yeah. Look where
you got it from.

02:00.421 --> 02:01.620
- I'm gonna miss you.

02:02.356 --> 02:03.721
(sniffing)

02:04.625 --> 02:05.823
- Mmm, your shirt smells

02:05.860 --> 02:07.025
Kind of musty.
- What?

02:07.094 --> 02:08.993
- Did you leave it sitting
in the dryer for too long?

02:09.029 --> 02:10.461
- You know what?
Let's hit the road, please.

02:10.498 --> 02:12.164
- You did. I'm sure you did.
- No, I didn't.

02:12.299 --> 02:14.766
No, I didn't, actually,
I laid it on top of the dryer
like you taught me.

02:14.835 --> 02:16.168
Can you just open the door,
please?

02:17.271 --> 02:19.037
- Richie, I'm glad you got
your own place,

02:19.039 --> 02:20.705
But you need to quit
that airport job.

02:21.975 --> 02:24.442
We both know it's bad news
over there. And right now,

02:25.646 --> 02:27.379
You got a lot of
good things going,

02:27.381 --> 02:29.181
So you need to keep your head
down and your nose clean.

02:29.316 --> 02:32.084
- I'm not leaving dane.
I gotta get him out of there.

02:32.086 --> 02:34.452
- Okay, richie,
this is not the time

02:34.522 --> 02:36.854
For you to be a hero, okay?

02:37.992 --> 02:39.925
Imma be that asshole right now

02:39.927 --> 02:41.926
That's gonna quote your
favourite movie back at you.

02:42.930 --> 02:45.330
"you're a good man
with a good heart,

02:45.465 --> 02:48.466
And it is hard for a good man
to be a king."

02:48.502 --> 02:50.669
- See, that was a mistake.
- Eh?

02:50.804 --> 02:53.071
- 'cause now you know what I
gotta say back to that, right?

02:53.807 --> 02:55.273
- What do you have to say?

02:55.309 --> 02:59.544
- I can decide what kind
of king I'm gonna be.

03:01.615 --> 03:02.647
Open it.

03:10.724 --> 03:11.656
- Mm-hmm...

03:16.597 --> 03:18.263
(gasping)
richie...

03:21.501 --> 03:23.302
- Yeah, I don't have
the receipt,

03:23.304 --> 03:26.371
So if, you know, you wanted
to return it, I'm sorry.

03:27.775 --> 03:32.044
♪ if I was king
for just one day ♪

03:32.046 --> 03:36.148
♪ I would give it all away ♪

03:38.319 --> 03:40.585
(indistinct chattering)
- ladies, I need a moment.

03:41.655 --> 03:42.988
- Oh god, do you think
she knows?

03:43.057 --> 03:44.289
- Knows what?

03:45.359 --> 03:47.326
- Like, knows that I
arrested adeline

03:47.328 --> 03:48.727
Before she was
actually arrested?

03:48.729 --> 03:50.996
Now, she's gonna fire me?
- Calm down.

03:50.998 --> 03:54.199
She's asking to see both of us.
She doesn't know anything.

04:04.544 --> 04:06.478
- I read your terminal v
reports.

04:06.480 --> 04:09.447
- Okay, that's great.
Fantastic, so...

04:09.449 --> 04:11.216
You're seeing what we're seeing?

04:11.218 --> 04:13.952
- What I'm seeing is a list
of their board of directors.

04:14.021 --> 04:16.755
A who's who of the most wealthy,

04:16.890 --> 04:21.026
Powerful, influential men and
women in the city. Big business.

04:21.095 --> 04:24.629
Politicians, cops, lawyers,
judges, you name it,

04:24.698 --> 04:26.765
They are on that board.

04:26.767 --> 04:30.234
So if and...
Whew, this is a big if.

04:30.271 --> 04:32.704
If you are gonna make this case,

04:32.839 --> 04:35.173
It has to be bulletproof.

04:35.209 --> 04:40.112
It has to be waterproof,
bombproof. Tsunami-proof!

04:40.247 --> 04:42.847
Every "t" crossed.
Every "I" dotted.

04:42.883 --> 04:45.249
Cover your asses, and mine.

04:45.286 --> 04:47.452
Tell me now if you don't
understand what I'm saying.

04:48.055 --> 04:49.187
(both): We do.

04:49.256 --> 04:50.955
- Okay. Shoo.

04:55.262 --> 04:57.228
- I'm the furthest thing
from bulletproof.

04:57.264 --> 04:59.664
- Later for that. Now, we focus.

04:59.667 --> 05:02.100
- Just how can I focus
when I'm this dirty,

05:02.102 --> 05:03.468
Dirty, dirty,
terrible, corrupt--

05:03.603 --> 05:06.138
- Hey. Don't wig out on me,
okay, wazowski?

05:06.273 --> 05:09.141
You did a bad thing,
but for a very good reason.

05:09.276 --> 05:13.145
And if you own up to it,
which you do not need to do,

05:13.280 --> 05:15.213
You'll get thrown off this case,

05:15.282 --> 05:17.282
And we will be down
one excellent cop at a time

05:17.284 --> 05:18.683
When we need her the most.

05:19.486 --> 05:21.253
Do you need a moment?

05:21.255 --> 05:24.089
- That's what I'm saying,
terminal v, five years
in the making.

05:24.091 --> 05:26.491
Deputy mayor briggs lobbying,
pushing through permits.

05:26.527 --> 05:28.593
Will french handling logistics
and construction.

05:28.729 --> 05:29.594
Hey.

05:31.365 --> 05:34.232
- Morning, detective.
- Uh, morning.

05:35.102 --> 05:36.434
- Okay, so...

05:36.503 --> 05:39.404
Now, we got pink cocaine
coming up from mexico.

05:39.406 --> 05:42.273
Local distributors include
bikers, mafia,

05:42.343 --> 05:43.975
And real estate agent
will french,

05:44.011 --> 05:46.310
Who we now learn
was figuratively in bed

05:46.347 --> 05:48.380
With deputy mayor marley briggs.

05:48.382 --> 05:50.916
Briggs has now opened up
a private airport terminal

05:51.051 --> 05:53.318
Five minutes from the gta
international airport.

05:53.320 --> 05:55.787
No checks and balances,
little to no security,

05:55.856 --> 05:58.055
And private planes coming up
from the us, from mexico,

05:58.092 --> 05:59.191
From south america.

05:59.193 --> 06:00.992
It's basically
the perfect gateway

06:00.994 --> 06:02.260
For cartel cocaine.

06:02.396 --> 06:05.397
Except we have nothing
on briggs.

06:07.067 --> 06:09.467
- We caught her daughter
with pink cocaine?

06:09.536 --> 06:11.770
- Mmm, okay. That's a maybe.

06:11.839 --> 06:13.004
- We have adeline in holding.

06:13.006 --> 06:14.306
We could take another
run at her.

06:14.441 --> 06:16.408
- Ooh, ooh, that's good.
I like that.

06:16.477 --> 06:18.944
- We've got michaels doing
security for briggs

06:19.079 --> 06:20.745
And doing favours
for the coyotes.

06:20.748 --> 06:23.948
I mean, that's not nothing.
- Mmm. That's not nothing.

06:24.585 --> 06:25.783
- It's a bold move.

06:26.720 --> 06:28.153
- Mama likes a bold move.

06:30.758 --> 06:32.423
(lawn mower whirring)

06:39.733 --> 06:41.432
(lawn mower powers down)

06:41.969 --> 06:43.235
(birds chirping)

06:47.074 --> 06:48.440
- Can I help you with something?

06:48.575 --> 06:50.542
- We have questions about
why you quit the force

06:50.611 --> 06:52.110
And started working
for deputy mayor briggs

06:52.245 --> 06:53.778
At her brand new private airport

06:53.847 --> 06:56.581
Which we believe is a front
for smuggling pink cocaine.

06:56.650 --> 07:00.919
- I was working as head
of security at terminal v,

07:00.921 --> 07:03.621
A job that I decided
to leave this week.

07:05.426 --> 07:07.659
- You quit? Why?

07:08.662 --> 07:11.663
- Because I prefer
mowing my lawn,

07:11.665 --> 07:14.332
And the job wasn't for me.

07:14.368 --> 07:16.201
- Gabrielle told us
that you forced her

07:16.203 --> 07:17.702
To drop zorka's charges.

07:17.704 --> 07:20.605
- And we also know you like
to do favours for briggs,

07:20.607 --> 07:22.874
And we know that
she's connected to the cartel.

07:22.876 --> 07:25.410
We're onto her, michaels.
It's only a matter of time.

07:25.545 --> 07:28.346
- So... We can bring you in
right now for interfering

07:28.348 --> 07:30.615
With zorka's fraud charges,
or we can all just, like,

07:30.617 --> 07:32.951
Sit down, you can tell us
what you know,

07:33.020 --> 07:35.620
Because your cooperation,
it really would go a long way.

07:36.890 --> 07:38.789
(birds chirping)

07:39.659 --> 07:41.392
- Allow me to put on some pants.

07:44.364 --> 07:45.964
<i> (pj): You have to calm down.</i>

07:46.033 --> 07:47.866
- I can't catch my breath!

07:47.935 --> 07:49.167
(door buzzing)

07:49.302 --> 07:50.802
My throat is closing up.

07:50.871 --> 07:52.237
- What's going on here?

07:52.239 --> 07:53.771
- She's allergic to the paint
on the walls.

07:53.807 --> 07:55.674
- Stuart, there's lead
in this paint,

07:55.809 --> 07:57.776
I can feel it off-gassing,
I can't stay here.

07:57.911 --> 08:00.778
- I'm not stu, and you're not
allergic to the paint.

08:00.814 --> 08:02.447
Sit down,
I got some questions for you.

08:02.449 --> 08:04.115
- I don't know anything,

08:04.184 --> 08:06.785
And I'm not faking it,
I have asthma.

08:06.920 --> 08:08.320
(breathing heavily)
and it gets worse

08:08.322 --> 08:10.455
When I'm tired or I'm hungry
and haven't eaten,

08:10.590 --> 08:13.325
Because pj will not feed me!

08:13.460 --> 08:14.926
- No, she wouldn't eat.

08:14.962 --> 08:17.128
She said she was allergic to
the peanut butter sandwiches.

08:17.264 --> 08:19.864
- Well, lucky for you,
you're moving out of
hotel holding tomorrow,

08:19.900 --> 08:21.266
And going to good ol' jail,

08:21.401 --> 08:23.001
Where you're gonna stay
until your hearing.

08:23.136 --> 08:24.402
- Why, stuart?

08:24.471 --> 08:26.771
- Because you're of no use
to us anymore.

08:26.773 --> 08:28.540
I mean, you don't know
anything, right?

08:29.943 --> 08:32.877
- No, you can't put me in a
place with a bunch of strangers.

08:32.880 --> 08:34.345
They're gonna get me.

08:35.215 --> 08:37.515
Coyotes could be
anywhere, anyone.

08:38.452 --> 08:40.985
He could be one.
- I am not a coyote.

08:41.054 --> 08:44.255
- Adam was in police custody.
They got to him, didn't they?

08:54.568 --> 08:56.301
(sighing)

08:56.436 --> 08:58.436
- Alright, listen to me.
I'll make you a deal.

08:58.438 --> 09:00.638
You cough up some solid evidence
on molina's connection

09:00.774 --> 09:03.240
To briggs, and I'll be
your transport.

09:03.277 --> 09:06.044
You want safe passage?
Work for it.

09:06.980 --> 09:09.714
- Ooh, ooh! Swish!
(laughing)

09:11.218 --> 09:14.252
- Yo. Something's
not right here, man.

09:14.254 --> 09:16.454
- Who cares?!
The hours are good,

09:16.456 --> 09:18.122
And we're making crazy money.

09:18.158 --> 09:20.525
Look, some suit from bogota
came through last week,

09:20.594 --> 09:23.261
Tipped me a c-note.
- Exactly.

09:24.264 --> 09:25.730
With money like that
thrown around,

09:25.799 --> 09:27.431
You really think there's not
gonna be a catch?

09:29.469 --> 09:31.069
- Then consider me caught up.

09:31.138 --> 09:33.572
- Let's start with
deputy mayor briggs.

09:33.707 --> 09:34.940
How did you meet her?

09:36.276 --> 09:38.442
- Fundraiser.
She was a city councillor,

09:38.478 --> 09:40.145
We were both rising
through the ranks.

09:40.280 --> 09:42.280
It was practical and political.

09:42.415 --> 09:44.282
She'd just been elected
deputy mayor,

09:44.351 --> 09:46.985
She called me for a favour.
She said a friend of hers

09:47.054 --> 09:49.821
Had been arrested
on minor fraud charges,

09:49.956 --> 09:51.489
And could I make them go away.

09:51.558 --> 09:55.026
- Zorka farkas.
- Then I got promoted to oce,

09:55.062 --> 09:57.762
And the next time I saw her
was when briggs' daughter
was arrested.

09:57.897 --> 09:59.297
- Is that why you got promoted,

09:59.299 --> 10:00.432
Because of deputy mayor briggs?

10:00.567 --> 10:03.567
- I don't know. I wondered.

10:03.604 --> 10:06.504
Then, you guys found
adeline's thumb drive.

10:06.506 --> 10:10.775
Evidence against enrique molina,
new head of the sinaloa cartel.

10:10.777 --> 10:12.210
When briggs heard about it,

10:12.212 --> 10:13.645
She told me to get rid
of the evidence.

10:13.714 --> 10:16.181
- Or?
- Or she'd tell shanks and hill

10:16.316 --> 10:19.184
That I'd misunderstood our
conversation about zorka farkas,

10:19.319 --> 10:21.386
And that I'd finessed
the fraud charge

10:21.388 --> 10:23.988
In an attempt to curry favour
with a person in power.

10:23.991 --> 10:27.258
- So instead,
you damaged crucial evidence
and framed me for it.

10:29.663 --> 10:30.862
- I'm sorry.

10:30.931 --> 10:33.865
I was stuck,
and I covered my ass.

10:35.168 --> 10:38.536
Maybe it hasn't happened
to you guys, but it happens.

10:43.377 --> 10:44.476
- Hey.

10:44.478 --> 10:46.344
Transporting adeline french?

10:46.479 --> 10:48.079
It's a bad idea, brother.

10:48.115 --> 10:50.014
- Yeah, well, I made a promise.

10:50.050 --> 10:51.349
Quid pro quo.

10:53.887 --> 10:56.620
Adeline and will shared
a safety deposit box.

10:56.657 --> 10:58.890
She gave me permission to go
in there without having
to get a warrant.

10:59.025 --> 11:01.493
The box contained
will's financial records.

11:01.628 --> 11:04.628
E-transfers from his private
accounts to adam gentle.

11:04.665 --> 11:06.364
Proof that he was laundering.

11:06.499 --> 11:10.334
Don't say anything just yet,
okay? I could really use a win.

11:13.040 --> 11:16.240
- Okay. But what does this have
to do with briggs and enrique?

11:17.444 --> 11:19.977
- This. The other half
of the puzzle.

11:21.648 --> 11:23.381
Adeline said that it's got
even more proof

11:23.450 --> 11:27.051
Of enrique's indiscretions,
plus all of gentle's records.

11:27.120 --> 11:28.920
Who got money when.

11:29.055 --> 11:30.722
Now, if she's right about
this thing,

11:30.724 --> 11:32.990
This could link every player,
including briggs, to the cartel.

11:33.026 --> 11:34.425
- Mm-hmm, have you looked at it?

11:36.396 --> 11:38.930
Let me guess.
You get her there safely,

11:38.932 --> 11:40.732
She gives you
the decryption code.

11:40.801 --> 11:42.266
I could decrypt
this thing right now.

11:42.302 --> 11:44.869
- No, I already tried, it's got
a dead man's trigger on it.

11:44.871 --> 11:47.138
Deletes itself if you run
any kind of software on it.

11:47.207 --> 11:49.207
I got the crown to give her
solitary confinement

11:49.276 --> 11:51.109
Up until the time
of her hearing.

11:51.111 --> 11:52.811
If I can get adeline
to grand valley,

11:52.946 --> 11:54.445
She'll give me the code.

11:54.481 --> 11:56.213
- This is dangerous, man.

11:56.249 --> 11:58.415
For you and her.
What if she's right,

11:58.452 --> 12:00.552
And the cartel does have
a price on her head?

12:00.554 --> 12:01.886
- You want to nail briggs
or not?

12:01.888 --> 12:03.788
- Of course.
But I don't trust adeline.

12:03.857 --> 12:05.222
She's gonna finesse you.

12:06.326 --> 12:08.159
Maybe I should--
- you should what?

12:08.161 --> 12:09.961
You should do this
instead of me?

12:09.963 --> 12:12.730
Okay, tough guy, 'cause what,
you can see through her game,
but I can't?

12:12.865 --> 12:15.233
- No, I'm a nice guy,
she will finesse the hell
out of me too.

12:15.235 --> 12:17.769
She's a master manipulator.
Let's just play it safe.

12:17.904 --> 12:19.370
Figure out a way to open up
the files,

12:19.439 --> 12:21.239
Let bloch and the etf guys
take her in.

12:21.241 --> 12:22.841
- I can handle her, okay?

12:22.976 --> 12:25.209
Believe me, I'm not as nice
as you all think that I am.

12:27.614 --> 12:30.381
<i> - You ever seen briggs</i>
<i> with members of the cartel?</i>

12:30.383 --> 12:34.451
Any mention of a coyote alliance
or any sign of pink cocaine?

12:34.488 --> 12:36.053
- I only worked there
for two weeks.

12:36.123 --> 12:39.056
The terminal is in soft opening
mode, I didn't see anything.

12:40.227 --> 12:43.528
- Soft opening. What,
there's a hard opening?

12:43.597 --> 12:45.797
- Yes, tomorrow.
- What do you mean?

12:45.932 --> 12:47.798
- There's a private
ribbon cutting

12:47.834 --> 12:49.900
With the board of directors,
and all the vips.

12:52.539 --> 12:53.738
What?

12:53.740 --> 12:56.107
- Brad, you are never
gonna be a hero, but maybe...

12:56.977 --> 12:59.143
Maybe you can be our inside man.

13:11.358 --> 13:12.423
- Deputy!

13:13.359 --> 13:15.059
Uh, they told me
you were in here.

13:16.229 --> 13:17.695
- What do you want, brad?

13:17.731 --> 13:20.965
- I made a mistake. I would very
much like my job back.

13:21.100 --> 13:23.835
I was adjusting to leaving
the force so abruptly,

13:23.970 --> 13:26.037
I made a rash decision,
very unlike me,

13:26.172 --> 13:27.839
And I apologize.

13:27.841 --> 13:30.074
- I'm sorry, you're too late.

13:30.110 --> 13:32.410
Jeff! I'd like to introduce you

13:32.479 --> 13:35.479
To my new head of security,
jeff keegan.

13:36.349 --> 13:37.582
- Hey, brad. Good to see you.

13:40.920 --> 13:44.255
- Our plan to use michaels
as the inside man didn't work,

13:44.324 --> 13:46.690
'cause guess who showed up
to take his place?

13:47.460 --> 13:48.759
Jeff keegan.
- Right?

13:48.829 --> 13:50.327
Just when you think
it couldn't get any worse.

13:50.363 --> 13:51.796
Okay, so, where are you guys at
with adeline?

13:51.931 --> 13:53.731
- Uh, nothing solid yet,
but I'm still working on it.

13:53.800 --> 13:56.467
- Naz even offered to transport
her to grand valley tomorrow.

13:56.536 --> 13:58.535
- What? Oh god, no, no, no.
That's a terrible idea.

13:58.572 --> 14:00.672
You can't transport a sociopath.
- What do you care, sam?

14:00.674 --> 14:02.974
- Okay, okay, guys?
Can we focus?

14:02.976 --> 14:04.609
Michaels said that
they're planning on doing

14:04.678 --> 14:06.678
A private ribbon cutting
tomorrow.

14:06.813 --> 14:08.879
Just the board of directors,
the vips...

14:08.915 --> 14:11.115
- So what about that?
We plant one of our team,

14:11.151 --> 14:14.752
Maybe as a vip, scout it out.
- Briggs has seen me,

14:14.754 --> 14:16.553
She's been here, so she's
probably seen every one of us.

14:16.590 --> 14:18.756
- But if briggs is in
as deep as you say she is,

14:18.825 --> 14:20.591
She's probably got a whole file
on each one of us.

14:20.627 --> 14:23.428
- Yeah, but even if you put one
of our people in to pose as vip,

14:23.563 --> 14:25.697
Michaels said that there needs
to be an introduction...

14:25.832 --> 14:26.631
(sighing)

14:28.101 --> 14:30.268
- Why the hell would
I call my mother?

14:30.337 --> 14:32.437
She hasn't visited me here once.

14:32.439 --> 14:34.438
Not one time.
- Sorry, lorraine.

14:34.474 --> 14:36.440
That must be really rough.
- Do you know what's rough?

14:36.509 --> 14:39.377
Prison. Prison is rough.

14:40.480 --> 14:41.645
- We might be able to
help you with that.

14:41.681 --> 14:44.249
- How? Can you get me like,
an extra soft mattress,

14:44.384 --> 14:46.984
